summary:
I started my carrier as a French language teacher at the French cultural centre in Nicosia, Cyprus.
After I moved to the Netherlands I worked for nearly 30 years in the airline industry for Olympic Airways/Airlines.
I worked in the passenger service area, followed by ticketing counter duties and finally moved to the operations department. I was responsible for all activities at the gate, managing a smooth turnaround time of the aircraft. Check-in supervision, catering, cargo and boarding were part of my duties.
I then moved to Service Wings where I was the dedicated staff of Cyprus Airways. I was responsible for activities to ensure smooth all-round ground operations.
Since nearly a year, I work for an agro food company where I am part of a research team that aims to develop a new source of proteins. Very innovative, creative and visionary work.
